## [FAIL] [AMBIGUITY/SCOPE] — `sendMailWithAudit` placement is left "open" but is the most call-graph-central new helper
**Where:** Spec DK-9, todo.md Phase D bullet "Add helper `sendMailWithAudit(...)` — could live in a new `src/lib/signup-mail.ts` or co-located in route. Spec leaves placement open; Generator chooses."
**Gap:** Both signup-routes import it. The Generator has 3 plausible places (in `mail.ts`, in a new `signup-mail.ts`, co-located in mitgliedschaft route + duplicated in newsletter route). Each choice has different test-mock surface and different coupling. Co-located = code duplication. In `mail.ts` = `mail.ts` becomes Node-only with DB+audit deps (can no longer be Edge-bundled). In `signup-mail.ts` = clean but the helper's testability depends on which file uses `vi.hoisted` mocks for which sub-deps.
**Implementation hazard:** Generator picks "co-located" → ~80 lines duplicated. Or picks "in mail.ts" → mail.ts pulls in `audit.ts`, `db.ts`, `submission-mail-texts.ts`, breaking the "pure transport" boundary the spec implies. Or picks `signup-mail.ts` but doesn't add a self-grep test like `auth-cookie.ts` has → no boundary-enforcement.
**Suggested fix:** Mandate `src/lib/signup-mail.ts` as a new Node-only module. Document its imports: `mail.ts` (transport), `mail-templates.ts` (render), `submission-mail-texts.ts` (load), `audit.ts` (emit). The two routes call exactly one function. Tests mock `signup-mail.ts` at the route-test layer (so route-tests assert call-shape) and mock `mail.ts` + `audit.ts` at the `signup-mail.ts` test layer.

