## [FAIL] [PATTERN VIOLATION] — `runtime = "nodejs"` is NOT currently set in signup routes
**Where:** Spec DK-1 hint "**Verifizieren** in DK-1 — falls nicht, hinzufügen", but no concrete must-have line
**Gap:** I verified via `grep -rn "runtime = \"nodejs\"" src/app/api/signup/` → 0 matches. Both `signup/mitgliedschaft/route.ts` and `signup/newsletter/route.ts` currently rely on default runtime (which is implicit nodejs since they import `pool` — but Next.js 16 may flip implicit-runtime defaults at any minor bump). After this PR they will also import `signup-mail.ts` which transitively imports `nodemailer` (Node-only). Without explicit `runtime = "nodejs"`, a future Next.js upgrade or Edge-runtime opt-in could silently bundle nodemailer for Edge → build failure.
**Implementation hazard:** Generator might miss the explicit declaration because both routes already implicitly work today. Then a future `pnpm update next` breaks staging-build with an opaque error.
**Suggested fix:** Promote DK-1 from "verify" to a hard must-have: "Add `export const runtime = 'nodejs'` at the top of `signup/mitgliedschaft/route.ts`, `signup/newsletter/route.ts`, AND `instrumentation.ts` (already implicit, but explicit-is-better). Add a static-source-grep test in `tests/lib/mail.test.ts` that asserts both signup routes contain `runtime = "nodejs"`."

