## [FAIL] [AMBIGUITY] — DEFAULT_TEMPLATES content + `tasks/m2-phase2-checklist.md` content are entirely under-specified
**Where:** Spec DK-7 "snapshot-Tests für alle 8 Defaults", todo.md Phase B "8 hand-crafted defaults"; DK-16 "(b) Mailu-Setup-Schritte... (e) Smoke-Test mit echtem Test-Send"
**Gap:** The spec doesn't say WHAT the 8 defaults should say. `member_confirmation_user.de.intro` should contain `[ZAHLUNGSDETAILS]` (placeholder for admin to fill in). But what's the boilerplate around it? "Hallo {{vorname}}, danke für dein Interesse an einer Mitgliedschaft..."? Generator has to invent text that's then snapshot-locked. Codex will not push back on boilerplate copy. BUT — the user (Huy) has strong opinions on tone/language ("alit — netzwerk für literatur*en" with the asterisk, French translation conventions, etc). Likely outcome: Generator ships, user reviews PR, asks for 30 copy changes, snapshots regenerate, +1 round-trip.

Same for `tasks/m2-phase2-checklist.md` — DK-16 lists 6 sub-points but doesn't specify the actual checklist content. Generator writes a stub, user reads it, asks for clarification on each sub-point.
**Implementation hazard:** Time wasted on generated copy that will be rewritten. Worse: user trusts the snapshot files and the actual deployed mails contain placeholder-quality text.
**Suggested fix:** Spec must include either (a) the actual 8 default strings in spec, or (b) explicit "Generator implements stub `[INSERT TEXT HERE]` strings; user provides finals during smoke-test phase, snapshot files updated then." Same for checklist. Avoid the user-review round-trip on subjective copy.

