## [FAIL] [TESTING/MEMORY-SAFETY] — `tests/lib/mail-templates.test.ts` snapshot files conflict with vitest-snapshot conventions
**Where:** Spec DK-7 "snapshot-Tests für alle 8 Defaults"
**Gap:** alit-website doesn't currently use vitest snapshot files (no `.snap` files in repo). Existing Vitest pattern is inline `expect(...).toBe(...)` or `toMatchObject(...)`. Adding 8 snapshot-tests creates a new convention with a new file-on-disk pattern. CLAUDE.md doesn't list snapshots in tools/conventions. Codex will likely flag "introducing snapshot-pattern not used elsewhere."
**Implementation hazard:** Snapshot drift between test-runs (tab/space differences, line-endings on Windows-checkout). Generator uses `toMatchSnapshot()` which writes `.snap` files — CI baseline differs from local. Or uses `toMatchInlineSnapshot()` which is fine but the test-file becomes giant.
**Suggested fix:** Spec must specify which snapshot mechanism: "Use `toMatchInlineSnapshot()` for the 8 defaults — keeps the canonical text co-located with the test. No `.snap` sidecar files." OR drop snapshot-tests entirely in favor of structural assertions ("subject contains 'Mitgliedschaft'", "html starts with '<!doctype html>'", "html ends with '</html>'", "html contains escaped vorname"). Snapshots are overkill for static defaults that won't change.

